## Review points

- Labels should identify app name, ownership, and component role consistently.
- Annotations should be limited to useful platform integration metadata.
- Ingress and TLS readiness need matching runtime controllers before becoming effective.
- HPA readiness needs metrics at runtime before it can make scaling decisions.
- Kyverno policy files are examples until Kyverno is installed and configured manually.
- Keep responsibilities separated: application manifests, Helm chart, CI, GitOps, and security review are generated by separate commands.
